cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.SD, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a fully automated white-box testing approach for RESTful APIs, which is a software engineering task. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of an evolutionary algorithm to automatically generate test cases, which involves programming language concepts. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with testing a service-oriented architecture (SOA), which can be seen as a system. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as the paper discusses fault finding metrics, which can be seen as a measure of the soundness of the system being tested. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper briefly mentions the challenges of testing a remote service over the network, which can involve security concerns.
